In [10]:
def retention_rate(x):
    if x['mau_previous_month']<=0:
        return 0
    return x['mau_both_months']/x['mau_previous_month']

df1['retention_rate'] = df1.apply(retention_rate, axis=1)

print("""Retention on active playlist: {:.2f}% """.format(
    df1[df1['mau_previous_month']>0]['retention_rate'].mean()*100))

Retention on active playlist: 63.01%

In [25]:
percentile_threshold = 99
columns_kpi = columns_activity + ['skippers', 'monthly_stream30s']
selected = np.array([True for i in range(df1.shape[0])])

for col in columns_kpi:
    threshold = np.percentile(df1[col],percentile_threshold)
    selected = selected & (df1[col]>=threshold)

df_top = df1[selected]
print('Percentage: {:.5f}%'.format(len(df_top)/len(df1)))

Percentage: 0.00596%

KPI by categories¶

In [27]:
def kpi_by_categories(cat_col, kpi_col, df, ax, title=' ', max_rows=np.inf):
    dfm = df.groupby(cat_col).agg('sum').reset_index().sort_values(by=[kpi_col],ascending=False)    
    nrows = min(len(dfm),max_rows)
    dfs = dfm[:nrows]
    sns.barplot( dfs[kpi_col], dfs[cat_col], ax=ax);
    total = dfs[kpi_col].sum()
    for p in ax.patches:
        percentage = '{:.1f}%'.format(100 * p.get_width()/total)
        x = p.get_x() + p.get_width() + 0.02
        y = p.get_y() + p.get_height()/2
        ax.annotate(percentage, (x, y))
    ax.set_xlabel(kpi_col + '_total')
    ax.set_title(title)

def generate_word_cloud(text_list, ax, title=' '):
    """Python program to generate WordCloud 
    """
    from wordcloud import WordCloud, STOPWORDS 
    
    comment_words = ' '
    stopwords = set(STOPWORDS) 

    # iterate through the csv file 
    for val in text_list: 

        # typecaste each val to string 
        val = str(val) 

        # split the value 
        tokens = val.split() 

        # Converts each token into lowercase 
        for i in range(len(tokens)): 
            tokens[i] = tokens[i].lower() 

        for words in tokens: 
            comment_words = comment_words + words + ' '


    wordcloud = WordCloud(width = 800, height = 800, 
                    background_color ='white', 
                    stopwords = stopwords, 
                    min_font_size = 10).generate(comment_words) 

    # plot the WordCloud image                        

    ax.set_title(title)
    ax.imshow(wordcloud) 
    ax.axis("off") 


    return ax
